  "target_response": {
    "text": "A flat 60% usually means the inputs are stuck, not the algorithm — and yours point at two things. First, HRV: 47 ms today against a 30-day baseline of 51.6 ms, and it has sat in that lower band all week. Second, resting heart rate: 59 bpm, about 1 bpm over its 30-day mean of 57.9. Sleep is the steadier input: 7.1 h a night, though still under your 7.9 h need. This combination often lines up with accumulated everyday load; you logged stress at 4 of 5 twice this week, so the pattern may not be tied to one identifiable bad night. The lever with the best odds: make tomorrow genuinely easy and protect the full sleep window, then watch HRV specifically for the first sign of movement.",
